<element number="eVitals.27"  minOccurs="1"  maxOccurs="1"  dataTypeName="PainScale"  isNillable="Yes">
<name>Pain Scale Score</name>
<national>Yes</national>
<deprecated></deprecated>
<state>Yes</state>
<definition>The patient's indication of pain from a scale of 0-10.</definition>
<v2Number>E14_23</v2Number>
<usage>Required</usage>
<performanceMeasuresGroup><performanceMeasure>Pediatric</performanceMeasure><performanceMeasure>STEMI</performanceMeasure><performanceMeasure>Trauma</performanceMeasure></performanceMeasuresGroup>
<v3Comment>The Pain Score can be obtained from several pain measurement tools or pain scale types (eVitals.28). The pain scale type used should have a numeric value associated with each diagram as appropriate. If the pain scale type utilizes multiple indicators/categories the total should be calculated and entered for the pain score associated with the patient assessment.</v3Comment>
<v3Changes></v3Changes>
<deprecatedComment></deprecatedComment>
